Le lundi, 20 octobre 2014 =C3=A0 17:19, Helmut Brandl a =C3=A9crit :

> How do I install ocaml by opam? The command 'opam install ocaml' does=20=
=20
> not work.

opam switch --help
=20=20
> What is the difference?=20=20

This will install an OCaml compiler from scratch in your .opam directory.
=20=20
> My ocaml system works fine and I don't want to
> compromise it because I need it.=20=20

This won't compromise your system compiler.
=20=20
> Can 2 versions of ocaml coexist without=20=20
> any interference?

With opam yes. See here http://opam.ocaml.org/doc/1.2/Usage.html#opamswitch

